<br>
Enchanters are known to be (in a roleplay perspective) to be charismatic, good looking, and you just don't want to say no to those types of people. Bards are also known to a lesser degree to have those same qualities. (Not much of a lesser degree, but still slightly lesser). When you look at Shamans you need to remember that they are normally the most important members of the tribe. How do they become the most important members and the most respected? I'd be willing to say it is because they have the high charisma to be able to discuss and sway people's feelings towards thier views.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't be surprised if a paladin also had Charisma as a green attribute in Everquest. Mostly because there are a few people who do enjoy the roleplay sense of the game, even though many will openly agree that there is none left. Everquest is a MMORPG, that means it is a massively multiplay online ROLE PLAYING game.<br>
<br>
At least that is how I see it, and no matter what someone says I enjoy having 240+ int and 240+ charisma, even though my other stats suffer greatly. And should ANYONE find a pair of red slippers an enchantress can wear please please please let me know. =)<br>
<br>
Lyena/Lara<br>
